        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 12:31PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 1231 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of showers
extending from near Sanostee to near Farmington, moving northwest at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 45 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Farmington, Shiprock, Kirtland, Nenahnezad, Fruitland, Ojo
Amarillo, Upper Fruitland, NAPI Headquarters, Sanostee and Flora
Vista.

This includes Highway 64 between Mile Markers 17 and 57.

This includes the following recreation areas...
Dunes Recreation Area, Glade Run Recreation Area, Head Canyon
Recreation Area, Thomas Canyon Recreation Area and Jackson Lake
Wildlife Area.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Blowing dust associated with strong thunderstorm winds can reduce
visibility below one quarter mile at times.</instruction>
